Date: Mon, 16 Mar 2026 10:09:34 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 1/5] fix(br): aggregate discovery outcome counts into snapshot
 counters (Block A)

- Add _aggregate_discovery_outcome_counts() function as SSOT for deriving
  diagnostic counts from raw discovery outcomes
- Modify _build_code_extraction_counters() to use aggregated counts when
  discovery_outcomes is present - aggregated values now take HARD precedence
- Restore hard invariant checks in CodeExtractionCounters.__post_init__
- Add explicit SSOT validation in builder to reconcile all counts when
  discovery_outcomes present
- rejected_non_business_subject_count tracked separately (from validation)
- Add new test file with 25 test cases covering happy/bad/corner/edge paths

Fixes issues:
- Aggregated outcome counts now override stale report_map values when
  discovery_outcomes present
- Hard invariants enforced to catch data integrity issues early
- Backward compatibility maintained for legacy inputs without discovery_outcomes
